ch Centre, Manesar, India under a grant funded by the Department of Science and Technology, Govt. Department of Science and Technology, Govt. of India. Should the child be at risk, a formal assessment by a clinical psychologist MUST be carried out for confirmation. The copyright for the screening tool is owned by Class should be in between 1 and 5 Years Months should be in between 0 to 12 Months should be in between 3 to 12 Select all languages of instruction Eye-sight test by a qualified ophthalmologist to rule out problems with vision. Hearing test by a qualified otologist to rule out problems with auditory processes. Detailed assessment covering different language domains by a clinical/educational psychologist in all languages of instruction. Recommendations At Risk Not at Risk Please provide additional comments for the child (max 200 chars) Drafts SOUND AWARENESS COMMUNICATION PRINT AWARENESS NUMBER CONCEPTS MOTOR COORDINATION BEHAVIOR MEMORY WRITING AWARENESS New Participant Screening language years and months. Medium of instruction Name* Child requires careful monitoring and supervision. Repeat screening after 3 months of remedial instruction The purpose of this screening tool is to identify children who may have learning disability, which hinders their school performance. The screening tool is designed to be comprehensive, so that it can be used as a referral questionnaire. If there is evidence that suggests a possible learning disability, the child will need to be referred for a comprehensive diagnostic assessment. Privacy Policy Privacy Policy READING WRITING MATHEMATICS and Validation, Testing and Cultural Adaptation Select different languages of instruction Email not registered Email already registered
